 silences—discovering along the way the power of dialogue to transform deeply held prejudices.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aCollege teacherszUnited StatesvBiography. 0aComposition (Language arts)xStudy and teaching (Higher). 0aEnglish languagexRhetoricxStudy and teaching. 0aHolocaust, Jewish (1939-1945). 0aIntercultural communication. 0aJewish college teacherszAustriazInnsbruckvBiography. 0aJews, AmericanzAustriazInnsbruckvBiography. 0aStudentszAustriaxAttitudes. 0aTeachingvCase studies. 4aEducation : Education. 4aHistory : Holocaust Studies. 4aHistory : World War II. 4aJewish Studies : Jewish Studies. 7aHISTORY / Holocaust.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z978311148737340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780791483596423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780791483596/original  a978-3-11-148737-3  SUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles